        <section class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 items-start">
            <div class="space-y-6">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900">1. Does everyone need 5 years?</h2>
                <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
                    The short answer is <strong>No</strong>, but it is complicated. The "5-year rule" is a statutory requirement for <em>Independent Escrow</em>, whereas for <em>Title</em>, it is a matter of administrative discretion.
                </p>
                
                <div class="space-y-4">
                    <div class="bg-white p-5 rounded-xl border border-stone-200 card-shadow">
                        <div class="flex justify-between items-center mb-2">
                            <span class="font-bold text-slate-800">Independent Escrow (DFPI)</span>
                            <span class="text-amber-600 font-mono text-sm font-bold">STRICT 5 YRS</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="experience-bar mb-2"><div class="experience-fill" style="width: 100%"></div></div>
                        <p class="text-xs text-slate-500">Financial Code ¬ß 17200.8: Manager must have 5 years of "responsible escrow experience."</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="bg-white p-5 rounded-xl border border-stone-200 card-shadow">
                        <div class="flex justify-between items-center mb-2">
                            <span class="font-bold text-slate-800">Title Company (CDI)</span>
                            <span class="text-slate-400 font-mono text-sm font-bold">FLEXIBLE</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="experience-bar mb-2"><div class="experience-fill" style="width: 60%; background: #64748b;"></div></div>
                        <p class="text-xs text-slate-500">Insurance Code: Focuses on "competence and integrity." Usually requires a track record, but not a hard 5-year legislative cliff.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-slate-900 text-white p-8 rounded-2xl flex flex-col justify-center">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-4 flex items-center">
                    <span class="mr-2">üí°</span> The "Manager Trap"
                </h3>
                <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-6">
                    In Independent Escrow, the 5 years must be <strong>consecutive and recent</strong>. If your manager has 10 years experience but has been out of the industry for the last 3 years, the DFPI may reject the application. 
                </p>
                <div class="bg-slate-800 p-4 rounded-lg border border-slate-700">
                    <h4 class="text-xs font-bold text-amber-500 uppercase tracking-widest mb-2">Pro-Tip</h4>
                    <p class="text-xs text-slate-300">
                        Most startups hire a "Manager of Record" solely for the application. Expect to pay a premium for their "qualifying" status‚Äîroughly $10k-$15k/month during the waiting period.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- SECTION 2: RESIDENCY & LOCATION -->
        <section class="bg-white rounded-2xl border border-stone-200 card-shadow overflow-hidden">
