                <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-800">Why CA is "The Island"</h3>
                <div class="space-y-4">
                    <div class="flex items-start">
                        <div class="bg-amber-600 text-white p-1 rounded mr-3 mt-1 text-xs">A</div>
                        <div>
                            <p class="text-sm font-bold">Dry Settlement vs. Wet Settlement</p>
                            <p class="text-xs text-slate-500">CA is a "dry" state. We don't fund at the table. Many states fund immediately. The DFPI considers the "dry" process more complex and requires CA-specific experience.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="flex items-start">
                        <div class="bg-amber-600 text-white p-1 rounded mr-3 mt-1 text-xs">B</div>
                        <div>
                            <p class="text-sm font-bold">The Escrow Law (Fin Code 17000)</p>
                            <p class="text-xs text-slate-500">CA has the most comprehensive escrow statutes in the nation. Experience in a state with "light" regulation (like NV or AZ) is often viewed as insufficient.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="flex items-start">
                        <div class="bg-amber-600 text-white p-1 rounded mr-3 mt-1 text-xs">C</div>
                        <div>
                            <p class="text-sm font-bold">Attorneys vs. Escrow Officers</p>
                            <p class="text-xs text-slate-500">Experience as a Paralegal in an "Attorney State" (like GA or NY) almost never counts towards the 5-year requirement in CA.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- INTERACTIVE CALCULATOR: WHAT COUNTS? -->
        <section class="bg-slate-900 text-white p-10 rounded-3xl text-center space-y-8">
